<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-08-23T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-08-23T06:00:00-05:00" n="690" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">195/609: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-08-23T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">August 23,
                                        1924—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received August 23—8:53
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>379. My 367, August 13, 4 p.m.<note n="41" xml:id="d690fn41">Not
                                printed.</note> Foreign Office has just informed me officially that
                            pending recognition by the French Government of the American Bureau of
                            Shipping, American vessels calling at French ports will in no way be
                            interfered with.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>